libdistance
------------------------------------------
The distance library is used to compare pieces of data for similarity.
Specifically, it contains a number of methods to find the edit distance between
inputs, or the number of differences between them. These differences are
calculated using various mechanisms. The inputs to these functions can be
character strings or arbitrary data.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.1-1
  libdistance-devel-0.2.3-1bl1
  libdistance0-0.2.3-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.32.0-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-6
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://monkey.org/~jose/software/libdistance/

Canonical download:
  https://monkey.org/~jose/software/libdistance/libdistance-0.2.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libdistance-0.2.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libdistance-0.2.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libdistance-0.2.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libdistance-0.2.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libdistance0-0.2.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libdistance-devel-0.2.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libdistance)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libdistance.README
  /usr/share/doc/libdistance/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libdistance/README

(libdistance0)
  /usr/bin/cygdistance-0.dll

(libdistance-devel)
  /usr/include/distance.h
  /usr/lib/libdistance.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libdistance.pc
  /usr/share/man/man3/distance.3.gz

